ter year than they had had in other schools. Test scores crept up a little, attendance improved, violent incidents decreased. &#10;I agree that trying something is better than doing nothing, but I think the education system suffers from the constant upheaval of &quot;THIS is the ultimate best practice, no, wait, THIS is the best practice!&quot; Some of these initiative which show a lot of promise are dropped before they're even given a chance to succeed. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="752" language="en" documentId="2126" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Chamalla" date="3/11/09 2:01pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://jezebel.com/5168107/same+sex-education-the-separation-debate?comment=11288024#comments" topic="single-sex-education" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="2126" notes="" title="Same-Sex Education: The Separation Debate"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="433"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="434" end="752"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>